# Source code overview

Entry points
- run_pipeline.py — orchestrates the full build and saves figures/tables.

Modules (src/)
- utils.py — paths, I/O, plotting defaults
- data_loading.py — CSV readers, schema checks
- sirs_metrics.py — normalization and term means ((x − 1)/4 to map 1–5 → [0,1])
- sentiment.py — VADER scoring and aggregation (compound −1..1; pos/neu/neg)
- models/fuzzy_model.py — Mamdani FIS (triangular sets; centroid)
- visualization/plots.py — figure builders
- pipelines/build_all.py — assembles steps and copies key tables to paper_tables/

Notes
- Large-class alignment: sections 01–10 aggregated as SYYYY-largeclass/FYYYY-largeclass.
- Reproducibility: outputs are deterministic under the pinned environment.
